data.title: 20 famous people from Delaware and where they live today
data.meta_description: There are several famous people from Delaware. Who are they, why are they famous, and where do they stay? Discover these popular people from Delaware here.
data.text:
Envying and admiring the biggest stars in the world is easy to do on social media. They share photos of themselves at exclusive clubs, rooftop bars, backstage parties, and restaurants where regular people can’t get reservations. However, some of them, such as the most famous people from Delaware, were born and bred outside Hollywood but have found superstardom, obscuring their humble beginnings.

Delaware is located in the Northwestern and mid-Atlantic parts of the United States of America. The state has multiple nicknames, such as The Diamond State, The Small Wonder, and The Blue Hen State. Apart from being a great state, it is home to some of your favourite celebrities.

Famous people from Delaware

Many celebrated personalities were born and raised in Delaware. Even though most of them have relocated to other places, they take pride in growing up in such a great place. But who are they? Here is a look at the top 20 famous people from Delaware according to Only In Your State:

1. Bilal Nichols

Bilal is one of the most famous athletes from Delaware. He is a popular American football defensive tackle for the Las Vegas Raiders of the NFL. He was born on 14 September 1996 in Newark, Delaware.

He played college football for Delaware before being drafted by the Bears in the 5th round of the 2018 NFL Draft. He resides in Las Vegas.

2. Elena Delle Donne

Elena is an American professional basketball player for the Washington Mystics of the Women’s National Basketball Association (WNBA). She was born on 5 September 1989 in Wilmington, Delaware.

Previously, she played for Chicago Sky from 2013 to 2016 and has bagged numerous titles for her excellence. The player still lives in Delaware with her partner.

3. Bill Press

Bill Press is one of the celebrities who live in Delaware. He is a popular American talk radio host, author, podcast host, and liberal pundit. He was born on 8 April 1940 in Wilmington, Delaware.

Between 1993 and 1996, he served as the chairman of the California Democratic Party. Now, he is one of the senior political contributors on CNN.

4. Joe Biden

Joe Biden is a renowned American political leader. He is the 46th and current president of the United States. Joe was born on 20 November 1942 in Scranton, Pennsylvania.

From 2009 to 2017, he served as the 47th vice president under President Barack Obama. Also, he represented Delaware in the US Senate from 1973 to 2009. He lives in Washington, DC.

5. George Thorogood

George is one of the famous musicians from Delaware. He is an American singer, musician, and songwriter. He was born on 24 February 1950 in Wilmington, Delaware.

He is a member of the Delaware Destroyers music band, which has released over 20 albums. The singer lives in California, even though he still has a home in Delaware.

6. Elisabeth Shue

Elisabeth Shue is one of the best actresses from Delaware. She was born on 6 October 1963 in Wilmington, Delaware, to Anne Brewster and James William Shue.

She is famous for her film and TV appearances in Adventures in Babysitting, Back to the Future Part II, The Saint, and Hollow Man. She lives in Maplewood, New Jersey, United States.

7. Aubrey Plaza

Aubrey is an American actress, producer, and comedian. She was born on 26 June 1984 in Wilmington, Delaware, USA. She is famous for starring April Ludgate in Parks and Recreation from 2009 to 2015.

She has also starred in Scott Pilgrim vs. the World, Scott Pilgrim Takes Off, and Legion. As of 2023, the actress resides in Los Angeles, California.

8. Valerie Bertinelli

Valerie is one of the celebrities who live in Wilmington, Delaware. She is a renowned American actress, cook, and TV personality born on 23 April 1960 in Wilmington, Delaware.

She rose to recognition after starring Barbara Cooper Royer in One Day at a Time from 1975 to 1984. She also appeared in Touched by an Angel and Hot in Cleveland. Today, she lives in Los Angeles, California.

9. Ryan Phillippe

Mathew Ryan Phillippe is an acclaimed American actor and producer. He was born to Susan and Richard Phillippe on 10 September 1974 in New Castle, Delaware.

He portrayed Billy Douglas in One Life to Live, Barry Cox in I Know What You Did Last Summer, and Keenan in Playing by Heart. Ryan resides in Los Angeles, California.

10. Teri Polo

Theresa Elizabeth Polo, known by the stage name Teri Polo, is an American actress born on 1 June 1969 in Dover, Delaware, USA. She starred Martha Focker in Meet the Parents and police woman Stef Foster in The Fosters and its spinoff Good Trouble.

She has also appeared in numerous other movies and TV shows. As of 2023, Teri lives in New York after listing her Manhattan Beach home.

11. Judge Reinhold

Judge Reinhold is an acclaimed American actor born on 21 May 1957 in Wilmington, Delaware, USA. He gained popularity for his exemplary performances in Hollywood films during the 1980s.

He appeared in Fast Times at Ridgemont High, Gremlins, and Ruthless People. He owns a beautiful home in Florida.

12. Ashley Biden

Ashley Blazer Biden is one of the most famous people from Delaware. She is a popular American activist, social worker, fashion designer, and philanthropist. She is the daughter of President Joe Biden and First Lady Jill Biden.

Between 2014 and 2019, she was the Executive Director of the Delaware Center for Justice. Today, Ashley and her husband live in North Philadelphia.

13. Bryan Stevenson

Bryan is an American lawyer, law professor, and social justice activist. He is also the executive director and founder of the Equal Justice Initiative.

He was born on 14 November 1959 in Milton, Delaware, USA. In 2021, he won the National Humanities Medal. Today, he lives in Montgomery, Alabama.

14. Jimmie Allen

Jimmie is an American country music singer and songwriter. He was born on 18 June 1985 in Milton, Delaware, USA. He was signed to Broken Bow Records, where he released two singles, Best Shot and Make Me Want To and an album, Mercury Lane.

He was dropped by the label in 2023 amid sexual assault allegations. The singer resides in Nashville, Tennessee.

15. Raul Esparza

Raul is one the famous actors from Delaware. Apart from stage acting, he is also a screen actor, voice actor, and singer. He was born on 24 October 1970 in Wilmington, Delaware, USA.

He is famously known for appearing in Company and Law and Order: Special Victims Unit. He has bagged numerous awards for his exemplary performances. Today, the actor lives in New York City.

16. Sara Dylan

Sara Dylan is a renowned American former actress and model born on 28 October 1939 in Wilmington, Delaware. She rose to fame for being the first wife of acclaimed American singer and songwriter Bob Dylan.

Sara starred Clara in Renaldo and Clara, but she is famously known for inspiring several songs by Dylan. Today, she lives in Los Angeles, California.

17. Donte DiVincenzo

Donte is one of the celebrities from Delaware. He is an American professional basketball player for the New York Knicks of the National Basketball Association. He was born on 31 January 1997 in Newark, Delaware.

In 2021, he bagged his first championship with the Milwaukee Bucks before he was traded to the Sacramento Kings. He is a resident of California.

18. Stephen Marley

Stephen Marley is a Jamaican-American musician, singer, and record producer. He was born on 20 April 1972 in Wilmington, Delaware. He is the son of highly acclaimed Jamaican singer Bob Marley.

Like his late father, Stephen has released amazing jams, too. He lives in Miami, Florida, where he has a home and a private recording studio.

19. Cynthia Rothrock

Cynthia is one of the renowned personalities from Delaware. She is an American martial artist and actress in Martial arts films. Before becoming an actress, Cynthia was a high-level martial arts competitor.

She was born in Wilmington, Delaware, but today, she lives in Scranton, Pennsylvania, where she works as a martial arts teacher.

20. John Gallagher Jr

John is an American actor and musician. He was born on 17 June 1984 in Wilmington, Delaware. He became famous after starring Moritz Stiefel in Spring Awakening, a 2006 rock musical.

The role earned him a Tony Award. He has released numerous songs and has appeared in various films and TV shows. Today, the artist lives in Brooklyn, New York City.

Famous people from Delaware - Final word

Delaware has been home to some of the most distinguished personalities in the United States and beyond. From TV actors to actresses, political leaders to star athletes, the most famous people from Delaware have greatly impacted the world.
